SIMPLE: sacramentarian
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sacramentarian
<hw>Sac`ra*men*ta"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>sacramentarius</ets>: cf. F. <ets>sacramentaire</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>A name given in the sixteenth
century to those German reformers who rejected both the Roman and the
Lutheran doctrine of the holy eucharist.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who holds extreme opinions regarding the
efficacy of sacraments.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sacramentarian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sacramentarian
<hw>Sac`ra*men*ta"ri*an</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
pertaining a sacrament, or to the sacramentals; sacramental.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the Sacramentarians.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sacramentary</ent>⟦br⟧
